label.value: Subglottic Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: FACT-O Questionnaire

value.value: A subscale complement to the FACT-G developed specifically for evaluating quality of life of ovarian cancer patients.

label.value: Pulse

value.value: Any of a series of intermittent occurrences characterized by a brief, sudden change in a quantity.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer in which the tumor is limited to the subglottis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with tumor extending to vocal cord(s) with normal or impaired mobility. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with tumor limited to the larynx with vocal cord fixation. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Asynchronous Multifocal Osteosarcoma

value.value: A bone osteosarcoma affecting multiple skeletal sites, with multifocal lesions discovered between 6 and 24 months after the appearance of the initial tumor.  Patients with asynchronous tumors have a better prognosis than those with synchronous osteosarcomas.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Subglottic cancer with tumor invading cricoid or thyroid cartilage and/or invading tissues behind the larynx (e.g. trachea, soft tissues of neck including deep extrinsic muscles of the tongue, strap muscles, thyroid, or esophagus). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Subglottic cancer with tumor invading prevertebral space, encasing carotid artery, or invading mediastinal structures. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Dye Laser

value.value: A laser in which light is emitted by a fluorescent organic dye and which can be tuned to radiate at any of a wide range of frequencies.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of supraglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: MPT Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of melphalan, prednisone and thalidomide used as induction therapy for plasma cell myeloma.

label.value: Cyclophosphamide-VAD Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of cyclophosphamide vincristine, doxorubicin and dexamethasone, used as induction treatment for plasma cell myeloma.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of supraglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of supraglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of subglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Intracortical Osteosarcoma
Subglottic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of subglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: VD Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of bortezomib and dexamethasone that can be used in the treatment of plasma cell (multiple) myeloma, systemic light chain amyloidosis and Castleman disease.

label.value: Dexamethasone/Lenalidomide Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of lenalidomide and dexamethasone that can be used in the treatment of plasma cell myeloma and systemic light chain amyloidosis.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with tumor limited to 1 subsite of supraglottis with normal vocal cord mobility. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with tumor invading the mucosa of more than 1 adjacent subsite of supraglottis or glottis or region outside the supraglottis (e.g., mucosa of base of the tongue, vallecula, medial wall of pyriform sinus) without fixation of the larynx. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with tumor limited to larynx with vocal cord fixation and/or invading any of the following: postcricoid area, pre-epiglottic tissues, paraglottic space, and/or minor thyroid cartilage erosion (e.g. inner cortex). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with tumor invading through thyroid cartilage and/or invading tissue beyond the larynx (e.g. trachea, soft tissues of neck including deep extrinsic muscle of the tongue, strap muscles, thyroid, or esophagus). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Low Grade Central Osteosarcoma

value.value: A low grade osteosarcoma arising from the medullary portion of the bone. It affects the long bones and is characterized by the presence of fibroblastic stroma and osteoid production. Pain and swelling are the usual sign and symptom. The prognosis is more favorable than conventional osteosarcoma.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with tumor invading prevertebral space, encasing carotid artery, or invading mediastinal structures. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Supraglottic cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm, but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with metastasis in two or more ipsilateral nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Supraglottic cancer with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Clear Cell Chondrosarcoma

value.value: A rare, usually low grade chondrosarcoma characterized by the presence of tumor cells with clear cytoplasm. It usually arises in the epiphyseal ends of long bones.

value.value: Supraglottic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer with tumor causing bone erosion or destruction including extension into the hard palate and/or middle nasal meatus, except extension to posterior wall of maxillary sinus and pterygoid plates. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)
